<event name="START_DIFFICULT_MENU">
	<text>Challenge levels alter the way you experience Multiverse. Once you've started your run, it cannot be changed! Challenge level configuration is saved across all runs until changed again.

The challenge level is independent from the standard difficulty slider in the hangar, and is a complement rather than replacement; it alters aspects that the default difficulty couldn't tweak itself.</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Casual.</text>
		<event>
			<text>[CASUAL MODE: A mode for people who just want to experience the gameplay in a relaxed way.]
			Starting scrap: 50~
			Starting fuel: 25{
			
			The Rebel ship at the sector one exit will not be an Elite.
			Renegade minibosses will never spawn, and Federation Outposts give free repairs.
			The Traveling Merchant always gives a sizable free gift, is weaker, and drops a powerful Energy Shield augment if killed.
			Will reduce the difficulty of the True Ending.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Return.</text>
				<event>
					<loadEvent>START_DIFFICULT_MENU</loadEvent>
				  </event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Standard.</text>
		<event>
			<text>[STANDARD MODE: plays the way the mod was originally designed.]
			Starting scrap: 20~
			Starting fuel: 12{
			
			A weaker Rebel Elite will await you at the sector one exit.
			Renegade minibosses will spawn with moderate strength and take scrap as tribute.
			The Traveling Merchant gives a small free gift in the Drop Point and Last Stand, and drops a powerful Energy Shield augment if killed.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Return.</text>
				<event>
					<loadEvent>START_DIFFICULT_MENU</loadEvent>
				  </event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Challenge.</text>
		<event>
			<text>[CHALLENGE MODE: A mode for people looking for a harder challenge, but without things getting too out of hand.]
			Starting scrap: none
			Starting fuel: 10{
			
			The Rebel fleet gains a 1 jump boost. Increases difficulty of the Elite at the sector one exit.
			Renegades minibosses are buffed and demand more scrap as tribute, Last Stand repair beacons will always be under attack by Elite Rebels.
			The Traveling Merchant never gives any gifts, is stronger, and drops a powerful weapon under most circumstances if killed.
